<section id="about" class="py-24 md:py-32 px-6">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
    <div class="reveal">
      <p class="font-mono text-accent text-sm mb-2">01. About</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-text-heading mb-8">
        Who I am
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      <div class="md:col-span-2 space-y-5 text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          I'm a senior software developer based in Orlando, FL, with <strong class="text-text-heading">8+ years
          building production systems in the Microsoft/.NET stack</strong>. My day-to-day
          is C#, ASP.NET, Azure, and SQL Server — designing, shipping, and maintaining
          enterprise software that handles real-world voice and communications infrastructure.
        </p>
        <p>
          I hold a <strong class="text-text-heading">Master of Science in Computer Software Engineering</strong>
          from Singidunum University, multiple Microsoft certifications (MCPS, MS: Programming in C#),
          and I'm a Mensa member. I combine formal CS training with deep hands-on experience
          across the full delivery lifecycle — from architecture and database design through
          CI/CD pipelines and production monitoring.
        </p>
        <p>
          Before software, I worked internationally — including three years at Emirates Airline
          in Dubai and a background in business economics. That path gave me something
          very valuable: <strong class="text-text-heading">the ability to translate between business
          stakeholders and engineering teams</strong>, and the discipline to deliver under pressure.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-card p-5">
